ques1:What do you mean by an Array
answer:Array refers to index collection of fixed number of homogeneous data elements.
->Single variable holding multiple values which improves readablity of th program.

ques2:How to create an Array?
answer:array declaration:(i) 1-D Array (ii) 2-D Array (iii) Jagged Array
1. Declaring and Creating an Array (Fixed Size)
int[] numbers = new int[5];  // Creates an array of 5 integers (default values = 0)
2. Initializing an Array at Declaration
int[] numbers = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};  // Creates and initializes the array
3. Creating an Array with new and Initializer
int[] numbers = new int[] {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};

ques3:Can we change the size of an array at run time?
answer:No, you cannot change the size of an array in Java once it is created.
Java arrays are fixed-size data structures.

ques4:Can you declare an array without assigning the size of an array?
answer:Yes, in Java, you can declare an array without assigning its size immediately â€” but you must assign size or values before using it.

ques5: What is the default value of Array?
answer:When you create an array in Java using:
int[] arr = new int[5];
Java automatically assigns default values to all the elements based on the data type.
| Data Type  | Default Value             |
| -----------| --------------------------|
| byte       | 0                         |
| short      | 0                         |
| int        | 0                         |
| long       | 0L                        |
| float      | 0.0f                      |
| double     | 0.0d                      |
| char       | \u0000 (null character)   |
| boolean    | false                     |
|Object types| null                      |

ques6:What is a 1D array with an example?
answer:A 1D (one-dimensional) array in Java is a linear collection of elements, all of the same data type, arranged in a single row (like a list).
Declaring and Using a 1D Array:
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Declare and initialize
        int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};

        // Access elements
        System.out.println("First element: " + numbers[0]);  // Output: 10

        // Modify an element
        numbers[2] = 99;  // Changes 30 to 99

        // Loop through array
        System.out.println("All elements:");
        for (int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
            System.out.println(numbers[i]);
        }
    }
}

ques7:Write a program on a 2D array?
public class Array{
	public static void main(String[] args){
		int nums[][]= {
					{3,9},
					{1,5},
					{8,9}
				};
		
		for(int i=0;i<=2;i++)
		{
			for(int j=0;j<=1;j++)
			{
				System.out.println(nums[i][j]+ " ");
			}
			System.out.println();
		} 
	}
}
